Che Smith (born July 6, 1977), better known by his stage name Rhymefest, is an American hip hop recording artist, writer, and humanitarian from Chicago, Illinois, whose first official album, Blue Collar, was released on July 11, 2006.

The song received the 2014 Golden Globe Award for Best Original Song and the 2014 Academy Award for Best Original Song.
